body: Oh turns out this is fixed in latest Psalm master (which has a bunch of improvements to `--diff`/`--diff-method`).

Firstly, feel free to merge the PR ‚Äì I can reproduce this trivially on master by clearing cache and just running Psalm on the single file `test/Unit/FixtureFactoryTest.php`.

---

This specific issue comes down to a hiccup around scanning, analysis and caching ‚Äì it's not related to `--diff` explicitly.

The bug originates in the PHPUnit plugin, and it happens because the plugin doesn't provide sufficient information to Psalm when Psalm is in the process of performing static reflection on the codebase.

The `Psalm\Codebase::classOrInterfaceExists` check assumes Psalm has visited every possible file containing a class or interface.

When analysing the full project, this is true, but when you're just analysing that single file, Psalm doesn't know it also needs to scan the file that defines `Ergebnis\FactoryBot\Test\DataProvider\NumberProvider`.

The plugin should do something like this: https://github.com/vimeo/psalm/blob/93735712f0f101ad4ea939fa9d915aba19c7b059/src/Psalm/Internal/PhpVisitor/ReflectorVisitor.php#L2093-L2094

Those two lines tell Psalm when it's scanning a file (essentially performing static reflection) that the file references a classlike that should also be scanned, if Psalm is to understand the file's contents properly.

That doesn't currently happen for `@dataProvider` annotations. For this to work as expected, The plugin would need to have some extra code in `afterClassLikeVisit` that parses each method's docblock and ensures that Psalm knows it needs to also scan classes referenced in `@dataProvider`.

cc @weirdan

@muglug so, to reproduce this, I would need:
1. Reference external data provider
2. Run psalm on the individual test file

right?
